flowRoot.flowPara: FABMoney is an open source digital currency for enabling collaboration in a FabLab. The project is completely open source: software, data, hardware, API, design. It is therefore another example of how one product or service can be made up fo completely open components and systems, and that Open Design can also be applied to the design of a currency.

The current version (0.3) is based on a personal RFID tag that each participant owns, and it is used for tracking the transaction between the users thanks to the RFID reader present in the device. Every transaction happens anytime a user want to thank another user for his / her collaboration in the FabLab: all the information about the transaction will be then uploaded to the central website where it will be available as Open Data. The central website will have Open API so it will be possible to always access this data. The data will be used for developing a map of the collaborations within the social network of the users, using the digital currency as a sign of the social capital of the FabLab community.
